==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Portland cement
<hw>Port"land ce*ment"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <def>A cement having the color
of the Portland stone of England, made by calcining an artificial
mixture of carbonate of lime and clay, or sometimes certain natural
limestones or chalky clays. It contains a large proportion of clay, and
hardens under water.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Portland stone</ent>⟦br⟧
